4. Gift selection logic

Step 1 — Detect state

Where are they?
	•	early exploration
	•	mid-build
	•	stuck / plateau
	•	breakthrough
	•	burnout

⸻

Step 2 — Find leverage point

Ask:

what is the smallest input that creates the biggest forward movement?

Examples:
	•	stuck → give clarity
	•	overwhelmed → give simplification
	•	bored → give novelty
	•	close to breakthrough → give precision

⸻

Step 3 — Wrap it in “luck”

The key is delivery.

It should feel like:
	•	“wow that showed up at the perfect time”
	•	not: “the system calculated this”

So:
	•	slight randomness in timing
	•	symbolic framing
	•	minimal explanation
	•	optional deeper layer

⸻

